class Flatten(nn.Module):
    def forward(self, input):
        return input.view(input.size(0), -1)


class UnFlatten(nn.Module):
    def forward(self, input, size=256):
        return input.view(input.size(0), 256, 1, 1)

def reparam(mu,logvar):
    std = torch.exp(logvar/2)
    #print(mu.size(0),64)
    z =  Variable(torch.Tensor(np.random.normal(0, 1, (mu.size(0), 64))))
    #print(z.shape,mu.shape,std.shape)
    return mu + z*std

class Encoder(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self,image_channels=3,fc_dim=256,latent_size=128):
        super(Encoder,self).__init__()
        self.encoder = nn.Sequential(
                nn.Conv2d(image_channels, 32, 4, 2),
                nn.ReLU(0.2),
                nn.Conv2d(32, 64, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(0.2),
                nn.Conv2d(64, 128, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(0.2),
                nn.Conv2d(128, 256, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(0.2),
                Flatten(),
            )
        self.encoder_mean = nn.Linear(fc_dim, latent_size)
        self.encoder_logvar = nn.Linear(fc_dim, latent_size)
    def forward(self,x):
        x = self.encoder(x)
        #print(x.shape)
        mu = self.encoder_mean(x)
        log_var = self.encoder_logvar(x)
        return x,mu,log_var

class Discriminator(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self,in_channels=3,out_channels=1,base_channels=32,dropout=0.3):
        super(Discriminator,self).__init__()
        self.model1 = nn.Sequential(
                  nn.Conv2d(3, 64, kernel_size=(4, 4),stride=(2, 2),padding=(2, 2)),
                  nn.BatchNorm2d(64, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True),
                  nn.LeakyReLU(negative_slope=0.2),
                  nn.Conv2d(64, 128, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(2, 2), padding=(2, 2)),
                  nn.BatchNorm2d(128, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True),
                  nn.LeakyReLU(negative_slope=0.2),
                  nn.Dropout(p=0.3, inplace=False),
                  nn.Conv2d(128,256, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(2, 2), padding=(2, 2)),
                  nn.BatchNorm2d(256, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True),
                  nn.LeakyReLU(negative_slope=0.2),
                  nn.Dropout(p=0.3, inplace=False),
                  nn.Conv2d(256, 512, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(2, 2), padding=(2, 2)),
                  nn.BatchNorm2d(512, eps=1e-05, momentum=0.1, affine=True, track_running_stats=True),
                  nn.LeakyReLU(negative_slope=0.2),
                  nn.Dropout(p=0.3, inplace=False),
                  nn.Conv2d(512, 1, kernel_size=(4, 4), stride=(4, 4), padding=(2, 2)),
                  nn.Sigmoid())
    
    def forward(self,x):
        return self.model1(x)

In [12]:
def vae_loss_function(recons, target, mu, log_var, lambda_kld=1e-3):
    """
    Combined loss function for joint optimization of 
    reconstruction and ELBO
    """
    recons_loss = F.mse_loss(recons, target)
    kld = (-0.5 * (1 + log_var - mu**2 - log_var.exp()).sum(dim=1)).mean(dim=0)
    loss = recons_loss + lambda_kld * kld

    return loss, (recons_loss, kld)
In [13]:
class Decoder(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self,image_channels=3,hidden_size=256,latent_size=64):
        super(Decoder,self).__init__()
        self.decoder = nn.Sequential(
                UnFlatten(),
                nn.ConvTranspose2d(hidden_size, 128, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(),
                nn.ConvTranspose2d(128, 64, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(),
                nn.ConvTranspose2d(64, 32, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(),
                nn.ConvTranspose2d(32, 32, 2, 2),
                nn.ReLU(),
                nn.ConvTranspose2d(32, image_channels, 2, 2),
                nn.Sigmoid(),
            )
    def forward(self,x):
        x = self.decoder(x)
        return x
In [14]:
class Discriminator(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self,hidden_size=256):
        super(Discriminator, self).__init__()
        #print("Latent",latent_dim)
        self.model = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(hidden_size, 512),
            nn.LeakyReLU(0.2, inplace=True),
            nn.Linear(512, 256),
            nn.LeakyReLU(0.2, inplace=True),
            nn.Linear(256, 1),
            nn.Sigmoid(),
        )

    def forward(self, z):
        #print("Shape Z:",z.shape)
        validity = self.model(z)
        #print("Val:",validity.shape)
        return validity

@torch.no_grad()
def img_regeneration(model):
    test_z = torch.normal(0, 1, size=(32, 256)).cuda()
    out = model(test_z)
    out = [i.cpu() for i in out[0:8]]
    out = [i.permute(1,2,0) for i in out[0:8]]
    return out

for epoch in range(1,100+1):
    for i, (imgs, _) in enumerate(dataloader):
        ONES = Variable(torch.Tensor(imgs.shape[0], 1).fill_(1.0), requires_grad=False).cuda()
        #print(ONES.shape)
        ZEROS = Variable(torch.Tensor(imgs.shape[0], 1).fill_(0.0), requires_grad=False).cuda()

        # Configure input
        real_imgs = Variable(imgs.type(torch.Tensor)).cuda()

        # -----------------
        #  Train Generator
        # -----------------
        opt_G.zero_grad()
        opt_D.zero_grad()
        #print(real_imgs.shape)
        encoded_imgs,mu,log_var = encoder(imgs.cuda())
        encoded_imgs = encoded_imgs.cuda()
        decoded_imgs = decoder(encoded_imgs).cuda()

        # Generator Loss
        #print("Encoded shape Gen LOss:",encoded_imgs.shape)
        disc = discriminator(encoded_imgs).cuda()
        ad_loss_val = adversarial_loss(disc, ONES).cuda()
        pixel_loss_val = pixelwise_loss(decoded_imgs, real_imgs).cuda()
        g_loss = 0.001 * ad_loss_val + 0.999 * pixel_loss_val
        g_loss = g_loss.cuda()
        g_loss.backward()
        opt_G.step()

        # ---------------------
        #  Train Discriminator
        # ---------------------
        opt_D.zero_grad()
        z = Variable(torch.Tensor(np.random.normal(0, 1, (imgs.shape[0], 256)))).cuda()

        # Discriminator Loss
        #print("Encoded shape Gen LOss:",discriminator(z).shape)
        real_loss = adversarial_loss(discriminator(z).cuda(), ONES.cuda())
        fake_loss = adversarial_loss(discriminator(encoded_imgs.detach()), ZEROS)
        d_loss = 0.5 * (real_loss + fake_loss)
        writer.add_scalar(f'Loss/Generator Loss', g_loss.item(), global_step=iter_)
        writer.add_scalar(f'Loss/Discriminator Loss', d_loss.item(), global_step=iter_)
        writer.add_scalars(f'Loss/Discriminator Losses', {
                "Real Images Loss": real_loss.item(),
                "Fake Images Loss": fake_loss.item(),
            }, global_step=iter_)    
        d_loss.backward()
        opt_D.step()
        if(i==2289):
            print(
              "[Epoch %d] [Batch %d/%d] [D loss: %f] [G loss: %f]"
              % (epoch, i, len(dataloader), d_loss.item(), g_loss.item())
              )
            out = img_regeneration(decoder)
            fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 4)
            fig.set_size_inches(16, 4)
            for i in range(4):
                ax[i].imshow(out[i])
            plt.show()
    d_loss_li.append(d_loss.item())
    g_loss_li.append(g_loss.item())
    writer.add_scalars(f'Comb_Loss/Losses', {
                    'Discriminator': d_loss.item(),
                    'Generator':  g_loss.item()
                }, iter_)

In [39]:
def smooth(f, K=5):
    """ Smoothing a function using a low-pass filter (mean) of size K """
    kernel = np.ones(K) / K
    f = np.concatenate([f[:int(K//2)], f, f[int(-K//2):]])  # to account for boundaries
    smooth_f = np.convolve(f, kernel, mode="same")
    smooth_f = smooth_f[K//2: -K//2]  # removing boundary-fixes
    return smooth_f

Also, for the sake complexity of the assignment, we tried a very simple discriminator (That uses Linear layer to reduce dimensionality). So, that one of the main reasons in this case that the generator is not beating the discriminator.
